<p class = "text-left"> 
Downhill Skateboarding originated from the huge surge of skateboarding that came in the 1950's and 60's in Southern California due to a respective surge in the world of surfing.
Over the years, different pursuits of skating stemmed creating cruising, park skating, street skating and my favorite: downhill skateboarding.
</p>
<br />
<p>
    Donwhill skatebording officially had its start in the late 90's with the intent that speed and steeze are the primary focuses. Over the next decade and a half,
    downhilling (as it is commonly referred to as in the community) never took the front seat of the skating world, but always had a seat of respect by the other skating disciplines.
    In the early to mid 2010's the rise of YouTube and other social media outlets finally gave those in my community a voice, but more importantly a facet to the world to see the thrill of skating down hills at around 50 mph.
</p>
