<p>
    I picked up this discipline when I was 14 with the sole intent to experience adrenaline at a degree that cannot be found while skiing, mountain biking or any other adrenaline-junky sport.
    Ever since, I have crashed a few dozen times both just on the road leaving road rash at 45 mph and into unaware drivers looking down at their phone blwoing through their stop signs.
    Though downhill skating is a dying sport and there are so few people a part of this community, individuals like Cole Trotta, Brandon DesJarlais and Sergio Yuppie keep the underground community alive and thriving.
</p>
